wiki.text:
'Planar' may refer to:



* Planar (computer graphics), computer graphics pixel information from
  several bitplanes
* Planar graph, graph that can be drawn so that no edges intersect (or that can
  be embedded) in the plane
* Plane (geometry), a name for something made up of flat planes or
  pertaining to planes
* Planar Systems, U.S. digital display manufacturing corporation based in
  Hillsboro, Oregon
* Zeiss Planar, photographic lens designed by Paul Rudolph at Carl Zeiss in 1896
* Planar device, computer hardware circuit in conventional PCI integrated into a
  motherboard
